WEBVTT

00:19.853 --> 00:20.687
Captain?

00:21.688 --> 00:24.482
Ortiz. Just musing a bit.

00:25.025 --> 00:26.109
Upon what, sir?

00:26.735 --> 00:30.196
The journey back to Spain,
the difficulty of it.

00:30.739 --> 00:36.161
Yes, the crossing to get here was hard.
Many men died.

00:36.161 --> 00:42.333
You weren't even first mate then.
Only after Pablo died of scurvy.

00:43.752 --> 00:44.836
I thought you...

00:46.087 --> 00:48.840
Pretty sure he also had scurvy.

00:50.091 --> 00:52.802
But what if we just...

00:53.928 --> 00:54.888
Just...

00:55.472 --> 00:56.639
Go back.

01:00.226 --> 01:04.189
Just to clarify, the captain is
talking about stealing the gold.

01:05.231 --> 01:06.399
Is he?

01:07.442 --> 01:10.820
Human life is short, but gold is eternal.

01:11.404 --> 01:14.324
And only God can possess the eternal.

01:14.324 --> 01:17.869
- The king may not agree.
- If he finds out.

01:18.912 --> 01:23.374
And at most, we're talking
about a series of misdemeanors.

01:24.375 --> 01:25.585
I am sorry, captain.

01:25.585 --> 01:30.340
I still think it makes us criminals,
and I could not live with myself if--

01:34.385 --> 01:39.724
Ortiz has died of scurvy!
I need a new first mate!

01:43.978 --> 01:46.231
Attention, everyone! Tie up the sails.

02:15.051 --> 02:17.428
Shit. Fuck...

02:19.931 --> 02:22.725
Ma'am. Ma'am, hey. Hi.

02:23.434 --> 02:25.436
Hey. Okay. Just...

02:26.688 --> 02:29.482
Hang in there.
Ambulance is on its way, okay?

02:30.233 --> 02:33.153
Do you want me to call someone?
Yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

02:34.445 --> 02:37.824
Oh, wait. No, shit.
Here, I need you to unlock your phone.

02:38.324 --> 02:39.617
All right. All right.

02:39.617 --> 02:40.535
Uh...

02:42.579 --> 02:45.331
Yes! Oh, fuck.

02:45.832 --> 02:46.958
Is it one of these?

02:47.584 --> 02:50.420
Oh, no, wait, wait.
That one was me. Mike. Mike?

02:52.046 --> 02:55.300
No, no, no! I'm calling.
Stay awake, stay awake. Fuck.

02:58.887 --> 02:59.762
Hey!

03:00.597 --> 03:02.098
I want my phone call now!

03:07.854 --> 03:09.439
About fucking time.

03:09.439 --> 03:10.481
Hey!

03:27.040 --> 03:28.750
<i>So where are Moss and Delly?</i>

03:28.750 --> 03:32.128
- What's happening at the dock?
- This was not the plan.

03:32.128 --> 03:34.547
No? This wasn't the plan?

03:36.507 --> 03:40.053
- Having me taken out by the police?
- You, yeah. Me, no.

03:41.721 --> 03:46.643
<i>That little suck Andy set me up.
He had me arrested.</i>

03:47.477 --> 03:50.063
For that old dude
that blew up in the porta-potty.

03:53.524 --> 03:55.818
And now thanks to him,
we don't have eyes on Moss.

03:55.818 --> 03:58.571
Moss is stupid, but he's not that stupid.

03:59.447 --> 04:03.660
If he saw us, both of us get arrested,
he's not going to the marina.

04:03.660 --> 04:06.204
- Which is why I used my call for Patsy--
- What?

04:06.204 --> 04:07.664
- Hey, hang on.
- You got a call?

04:07.664 --> 04:10.041
Shut up. Yes, I got a fucking phone call
and I called Patsy.

04:11.042 --> 04:13.086
So that her family could get out.

04:14.212 --> 04:15.088
Did she?

04:17.966 --> 04:20.551
- I don't know. She didn't answer.
- Shit.

04:22.387 --> 04:24.180
We don't know what that means.

04:24.681 --> 04:26.724
- Oh, come on.
- We don't.

04:27.308 --> 04:29.644
- Are you kidding me?
- It doesn't mean anything.

04:29.644 --> 04:32.063
It means that she wouldn't be in danger

04:32.063 --> 04:34.857
if you hadn't gotten me arrested
so you could take the gold.

04:34.857 --> 04:37.777
What's wrong with you?
Why do you always think the worst of me?

04:37.777 --> 04:39.821
I find it a very useful place to start.

04:39.821 --> 04:43.074
I had you arrested
because I didn't want you to kill Moss.

04:43.074 --> 04:45.952
Oh, what fucking bullshit.

04:45.952 --> 04:48.997
Bullshit? I wanted you to let us do it.

04:48.997 --> 04:52.959
- Why do you care so much about who did it?
- Because you're my son!

04:54.252 --> 04:56.754
It's a bridge I did not want you to cross.

04:59.173 --> 05:03.261
- I was a cop.
- And that's completely different, okay?

05:04.387 --> 05:07.015
Some old man dies,
some guy blowing up in a porta-potty,

05:07.015 --> 05:10.143
that's collateral damage, okay?
That shit happens.

05:10.143 --> 05:12.478
But you picking up a gun

05:13.104 --> 05:16.065
and shooting a guy
because you want him dead...

05:18.609 --> 05:20.570
that's something you don't come back from.

05:35.501 --> 05:37.795
Okay, Valentine. You made bail.

05:38.296 --> 05:39.339
Aha!

05:40.131 --> 05:41.841
- Of course he did.
- Yeah.

05:41.841 --> 05:45.094
- Right this way, sir.
- Shut up. Patsy got my message.

05:48.681 --> 05:51.017
Whoa, not you Valentine.

05:51.642 --> 05:52.602
Him Valentine.

05:54.979 --> 05:55.813
Let's go.

06:04.739 --> 06:06.240
<i>Yes. Hello, sir.</i>

06:06.240 --> 06:10.203
<i>Uh, this is Randy from the marina.
The lady cop's been shot.</i>

06:10.953 --> 06:13.122
<i>Yeah, she can't talk right now.</i>

06:13.122 --> 06:15.833
<i>It's pretty bad. She's bleeding a lot.</i>

06:15.833 --> 06:18.795
<i>And there's another guy here.
I think he's dead.</i>

06:18.795 --> 06:20.838
<i>I don't know. I don't wanna look.</i>

06:20.838 --> 06:22.632
<i>- Uh...</i>

06:22.632 --> 06:24.217
<i>Here! Here! Over here!</i>

06:29.931 --> 06:33.309
There's the reaction I wanted before.

06:33.309 --> 06:35.144
Surprise.

06:35.978 --> 06:38.981
- You shot Iris?
- No. Who's Iris?

06:39.565 --> 06:40.483
At the dock.

06:41.609 --> 06:42.693
Did you shoot her?

06:43.402 --> 06:46.405
No. I didn't go to the dock

06:46.405 --> 06:49.534
because we figured out
your little ambush plan.

06:50.326 --> 06:52.703
But don't say thanks
for bailing you out or anything.

06:52.703 --> 06:55.456
Fuck you. I need to get to the hospital.
What the fuck?

06:58.334 --> 07:00.461
You might end up there later.

07:00.461 --> 07:02.547
But you got work to do first.

07:09.137 --> 07:12.515
Let's go. All right? Come on. Come on.

07:18.187 --> 07:19.355
Get in.

07:19.355 --> 07:20.648
Iris has been shot.

07:20.648 --> 07:23.025
Tell this asshole
I need to get to the hospital.

07:23.025 --> 07:25.319
I get why you're upset.

07:25.319 --> 07:27.280
The wrong girl taking the bullet and all.

07:29.198 --> 07:30.908
What are you gonna do anyway?

07:31.742 --> 07:33.411
You're not a doctor.

07:33.411 --> 07:35.371
All you are is a driver.

07:41.419 --> 07:43.463
Now, take me to the fucking gold.

07:44.255 --> 07:46.299
Where it really is this time.

08:12.825 --> 08:15.077
Oh, I got you.

08:16.370 --> 08:18.206
Goddamn it! Andy!

08:18.206 --> 08:20.124
Just hold your horses, chief.

08:20.708 --> 08:25.254
- Oh, finally.
- I'm sorry I missed Mike in here with you.

08:25.254 --> 08:27.465
That would have been
a picture for your Christmas card.

08:30.968 --> 08:34.472
I don't know what bug you got up your ass,
but we can work it out later.

08:34.472 --> 08:37.099
No, no, no. You're good where you're at.

08:37.099 --> 08:38.976
I'm just here to visit.

08:49.362 --> 08:54.116
Look, I don't know
what you think I've done,

08:55.576 --> 08:57.286
but you need to listen to me.

08:57.286 --> 08:58.496
No, no.

08:59.247 --> 09:01.499
We're gonna do this
the other way around for once.

09:02.833 --> 09:06.420
See, what you did is you broke my heart.

09:08.839 --> 09:11.092
I tried to count them all up,

09:11.092 --> 09:13.344
the times I looked the other way,

09:13.344 --> 09:16.806
even when you didn't have
enough respect for me

09:16.806 --> 09:19.183
to bother to hide what you were up to.

09:19.183 --> 09:22.728
I told myself,
"It's nothing serious. Where's the harm?

09:22.728 --> 09:25.815
The old man's just making
a few extra bucks off smuggled cigars

09:25.815 --> 09:28.192
or maybe something a little stronger
now and then."

09:28.818 --> 09:31.195
- But you owe me.
- I owe you?

09:32.530 --> 09:33.614
Because what?

09:34.949 --> 09:36.576
I hurt your feelings?

09:37.785 --> 09:42.623
So you bring me in here,
and you bust me on some bullshit charges

09:42.623 --> 09:45.334
about some guy
who died from taking a crap?

09:48.671 --> 09:50.756
Man, that's not why you're in here.

09:55.761 --> 09:56.971
You know this guy?

09:58.806 --> 09:59.890
Whoo!

10:02.059 --> 10:03.477
- Fuck yeah!

10:03.477 --> 10:06.606
Woo-hoo! Woo-hoo!

10:06.606 --> 10:07.523
Yeah!

10:08.691 --> 10:12.820
- Never seen him before in my life.
- Yeah, he didn't know you either.

10:13.529 --> 10:17.033
But luckily,
in this closed system of ours,

10:17.033 --> 10:20.786
that being the underbelly
of Central Florida street drug crime,

10:21.621 --> 10:23.497
everybody knows somebody.

10:23.998 --> 10:27.126
So I give the cops
who I bought the drugs from,

10:27.835 --> 10:29.003
and I get a deal?

10:29.003 --> 10:30.880
I tell you my supplier and I walk.

10:30.880 --> 10:32.381
We don't meet in person.

10:32.882 --> 10:36.344
All I know is once my product comes in,
it goes up river on a boat.

10:37.637 --> 10:38.679
Whose boat?

10:39.555 --> 10:41.766
She's speedy, I'll give you that.

10:42.725 --> 10:43.601
Take care now.

10:45.645 --> 10:47.313
<i>It's like that funny poster you see,</i>

10:47.313 --> 10:50.483
where, one after the other,
a little fish gets eaten by a bigger fish,

10:51.067 --> 10:52.443
except the opposite.

10:52.943 --> 10:55.780
See, you got eaten
by the littlest fish of all.

10:55.780 --> 10:58.491
- You can't do this.
This isn't me.

10:58.491 --> 11:00.076
This is the DEA.

11:01.035 --> 11:04.163
- And that's federal.
My daughter's life is at stake.

11:04.163 --> 11:05.706
You need to help me.

11:05.706 --> 11:09.418
Oh, I don't, actually.

11:10.419 --> 11:13.714
This relationship is no longer symbiotic.

11:15.132 --> 11:16.592
But I'll call Patsy,

11:18.260 --> 11:19.804
and you call a lawyer.

11:27.978 --> 11:29.230
These are the floats.

11:29.230 --> 11:34.110
We dive down, we attach them
to each corner of the truck and the tires,

11:35.236 --> 11:36.654
inflate them with the compressor,

11:37.738 --> 11:39.240
the truck pops up,

11:39.240 --> 11:42.076
and then we float her to shore
like a fucking raft.

11:42.076 --> 11:43.285
Watch your step.

11:43.285 --> 11:46.872
We wouldn't want you to slip
and hurt yourself before we get started.

11:46.872 --> 11:48.207
Thanks. Now give me the phone.

11:48.207 --> 11:50.167
- I need to call the hospital.
Eh...

11:50.918 --> 11:52.753
I changed my mind on that.

11:52.753 --> 11:55.881
I feel like you'll work harder
if I let you call after.

11:56.507 --> 11:58.467
So get to work.

11:59.760 --> 12:02.138
It was supposed to be a four-man job.

12:02.763 --> 12:05.724
Then I guess
you'll have to work four times harder.

12:21.490 --> 12:26.996
My dad never-- What do you call it?
- groomed me for this.

12:26.996 --> 12:30.416
He never said,
"Son, someday all of this will be yours."

12:32.042 --> 12:33.252
It just was.

12:36.380 --> 12:42.011
Then everybody was looking at me
like the only thing I was, was not him.

12:48.142 --> 12:49.643
Everybody except you.

12:53.189 --> 12:55.399
You made me think I could be someone.

12:57.067 --> 12:58.402
You pulled me through.

13:03.866 --> 13:04.700
Same.

13:48.619 --> 13:50.162
Wait. Wait.

13:50.913 --> 13:51.956
Is it all ready?

13:53.582 --> 13:56.835
- You just have to turn on the compressor.
- Oh. Let me do it.

13:56.835 --> 13:59.463
I mean, I should earn my share, right?

14:01.215 --> 14:02.174
Red button.

14:03.551 --> 14:04.426
Just push it.

14:42.715 --> 14:44.341
Woo-hoo!

14:44.341 --> 14:47.803
- Did you see that? That's fucking awesome!
- Moss!

14:47.803 --> 14:49.722
That's fucking awesome. Hey.

15:12.411 --> 15:13.746
Come on.

15:33.974 --> 15:34.808
One thing.

15:36.143 --> 15:38.312
Hey, hey. Don't you pop that.

15:38.312 --> 15:41.065
I might, though. And down it goes.

15:41.565 --> 15:44.360
- Put the fucking knife away.
- Is shooting it any better?

15:49.406 --> 15:52.493
He won't sink it.
He wants the gold as much as I do.

15:53.827 --> 15:55.996
- More.
- Okay. What?

15:55.996 --> 15:57.373
So this gold...

15:58.415 --> 16:01.085
What's the split? A third each?

16:02.294 --> 16:06.173
Here's the split.
I take it all and I let you live.

16:07.132 --> 16:10.010
Counting on my will to live
is a sucker bet.

16:10.511 --> 16:14.056
How do you feel about your sister?
Be honest with yourself.

16:15.015 --> 16:17.184
You know
you'll never manage to pay me back,

16:17.184 --> 16:19.061
not if you live to be 100.

16:19.061 --> 16:21.105
So you know I'm being generous

16:21.105 --> 16:23.273
when I say
I will give you exactly as much gold

16:23.273 --> 16:25.359
as you need to pay me back for all that.

16:26.568 --> 16:29.863
And then we're square,
and your family is safe.

16:30.823 --> 16:32.032
On my word of honor.

16:34.535 --> 16:35.369
Mike.

16:36.412 --> 16:40.040
You've been saying this whole time
all you want is out, right?

16:50.634 --> 16:51.844
I should have gotten out

16:51.844 --> 16:54.722
the night you crawled back
into my motel room like a snake.

17:44.646 --> 17:47.566
Fucking gamblers, man.

17:48.150 --> 17:50.986
- There's nothing.
- It was always nothing.

17:50.986 --> 17:53.989
You're all the same, man.
Every one of you.

17:53.989 --> 17:55.866
Chasing some empty truck.

17:56.366 --> 17:59.369
You know what? I changed my mind.

17:59.870 --> 18:01.914
You can have all the gold.

18:03.832 --> 18:05.793
There's still the matter of your debt.

18:05.793 --> 18:09.046
I'm afraid I gotta settle it
the same way I settled Gil's.

18:09.046 --> 18:11.965
The two of you can have a laugh
over all this when you meet.

18:14.593 --> 18:16.512
I thought you didn't kill Gil.

18:16.512 --> 18:17.805
I didn't.

18:17.805 --> 18:20.974
That's right. He hasn't killed anyone
personally since my father.

18:20.974 --> 18:23.811
Because my dad told me to do it.

18:23.811 --> 18:25.104
We went over this.

18:25.104 --> 18:28.398
Just like Jimmy killed Gil
because I told him to do it.

18:28.398 --> 18:30.859
That's how the boss-employee
relationship works.

19:38.093 --> 19:39.928
You know what, Mike?

19:40.512 --> 19:41.680
Let me tell you why--

19:56.153 --> 19:57.696
Look what you made me do.

19:59.907 --> 20:01.158
Him or me?

20:05.621 --> 20:06.622
All of you.

20:12.794 --> 20:14.504
I do have a question, though.

20:17.716 --> 20:20.260
If you had that gun,
why didn't you use it before?

20:20.260 --> 20:23.222
Sure, and when would have been good?
At your sister's house?

20:23.764 --> 20:26.308
Or in the car
driving down the highway with a gun on me?

20:26.308 --> 20:27.809
Or in front of the police station?

20:27.809 --> 20:29.853
Plus, who I might actually have to shoot,

20:29.853 --> 20:33.523
since you were happy
to let me drive blindly into an ambush.

20:33.523 --> 20:36.777
- I thought you were with him.
- I know you did, and fuck you for that!

20:36.777 --> 20:39.404
I heard you in his motel room, Delly.

20:40.322 --> 20:42.032
- When?
- This afternoon.

20:42.032 --> 20:45.077
- You told him that you've been playing me.
- To save your life!

20:49.581 --> 20:51.208
Well, I know that now.

20:52.376 --> 20:53.585
Is that a thank you?

20:58.590 --> 20:59.424
Thank you.

21:12.020 --> 21:12.854
Freeze.

21:14.064 --> 21:15.190
Dude, I have the gun.

21:15.190 --> 21:17.985
I know you have the gun
'cause it's my goddamn gun!

21:17.985 --> 21:20.529
- What?
- Deputy Ketcher?

21:20.529 --> 21:21.446
Yeah.

21:22.072 --> 21:23.490
Wait, you know this guy?

21:24.533 --> 21:27.327
He's right. It's his gun. I stole it.

21:27.953 --> 21:29.204
Hard to mistake it.

21:29.830 --> 21:31.456
Wait, so he's a cop?

21:31.456 --> 21:33.500
- Yeah.
- Because, seriously...

21:35.043 --> 21:37.921
I don't care about that, okay?
I really don't.

21:39.006 --> 21:41.550
I'm not gonna go into everything
that's happened the last few days,

21:41.550 --> 21:43.218
except to say I have a new understanding

21:43.218 --> 21:45.345
for people living
on the margins of society.

21:46.596 --> 21:50.851
I did have a finger up my ass,
but all I wanted was a gun.

21:51.435 --> 21:52.436
That's it.

21:52.436 --> 21:55.522
You wouldn't think that would be
hard to get in Florida after all.

21:55.522 --> 21:57.357
But of course
I had to pick a murder weapon,

21:57.357 --> 22:00.277
which in retrospect was probably
also inevitable, given the odds.

22:00.277 --> 22:02.863
I probably rode past three or four of them

22:02.863 --> 22:04.865
by the side of the road on the way here.

22:04.865 --> 22:08.410
But right now,
I swear to you beyond any doubt,

22:08.410 --> 22:10.871
I have zero interest in either one of you.

22:10.871 --> 22:15.292
All I want right now in the whole world
is my gun back

22:15.292 --> 22:17.711
and to get the fuck out of Florida.

22:17.711 --> 22:21.423
Problem is, your gun
is now a murder weapon.

22:22.049 --> 22:24.051
And there's a bullet missing.

22:24.718 --> 22:27.763
A bullet from your personal weapon
inside a murder victim.

22:27.763 --> 22:30.640
That's something you don't want,
and you should take that too.

22:32.726 --> 22:35.437
- From his head?
- No, it probably went through.

22:37.939 --> 22:39.066
What was the angle?

22:40.984 --> 22:42.611
Right where she's standing.

22:44.321 --> 22:46.615
It could be lodged in that truck.

22:46.615 --> 22:49.201
Yeah, or maybe it ricocheted. There, look.

23:00.462 --> 23:02.130
- Here.
- Thank you very much.

23:02.839 --> 23:05.592
Hey, can you give me a hand before you go?

23:05.592 --> 23:07.344
Sure. With what?

23:41.419 --> 23:42.963
You wanna say something?

23:43.922 --> 23:46.466
My father told me
never to speak ill of the dead.

23:47.634 --> 23:50.178
But then
that degenerate fucker killed him.

24:06.695 --> 24:07.529
Thank you.

24:08.697 --> 24:09.739
Oh.

24:10.407 --> 24:12.367
I don't have enough money
for the bus home.

24:12.367 --> 24:14.452
That sucks, but it's not our problem.

24:16.121 --> 24:17.247
Sorry.

24:30.886 --> 24:31.928
Look left.

24:33.180 --> 24:34.514
- Look forward.

24:44.441 --> 24:46.234
Okay, now can we go?

24:52.199 --> 24:53.283
What?

24:56.578 --> 24:57.954
We have to make a stop.

25:01.625 --> 25:02.459
No.

25:04.294 --> 25:05.670
I need to go to the hospital.

25:06.630 --> 25:08.006
Are you fucking kidding me?

25:08.006 --> 25:09.549
To see if Iris is okay.

25:09.549 --> 25:11.968
- So call her.
- It's my fault she's hurt.

25:12.677 --> 25:13.929
But it's not mine.

25:13.929 --> 25:15.847
I need to give her the tape of Moss.

25:15.847 --> 25:17.015
What tape?

25:18.558 --> 25:19.768
Him confessing to murder.

25:19.768 --> 25:22.187
You have me doing murder. Give me that.

25:22.187 --> 25:23.772
I'll erase your part. Don't worry.

25:23.772 --> 25:24.814
Will you?

25:26.107 --> 25:28.193
- What do you mean, will I?
- I don't know, Mike.

25:29.361 --> 25:32.280
I just know
how many times I've sat around waiting

25:32.280 --> 25:36.159
while you take care of your needs,
and your wants,

25:36.159 --> 25:39.955
and your sister, and your ex-wife,
and now it's my turn, me.

25:39.955 --> 25:41.915
I need. I--

25:41.915 --> 25:45.335
I just fucking killed someone for you,
